-- AIRSHOW-Safran says Hainan Airlines engine deal to be worth $1.3 bln
-- By Victoria Bryan
-- Wed Jul 16, 2014 09:34AM EDT
-- None



FARNBOROUGH, England, July 16 (Reuters) - Safran <SAF.PA> said an order from China's Hainan Airlines <600221.SS> to supply CFM International engines to power 50 Boeing <BA.N> 737 MAX 8 planes will be worth $1.3 billion at list prices.

The carrier announced the commitment to buy the narrow-body planes at Farnborough Airshow earlier on Wednesday. The purchase is subject to approval from the Chinese government.